{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775899425512,"sessionID":"ses_2842c4eeeffe5EI9bM3M8UmhOg","part":{"id":"prt_d7bd5964c001PbOtelvvl6J2uq","messageID":"msg_d7bd58cd4001yjvhJf7aoZPrrz","sessionID":"ses_2842c4eeeffe5EI9bM3M8UmhOg","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:13","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","content":"# Proposal: K8s/AgentCube Provider (AR-026)\n\n## AR-026 — K8s/AgentCube Provider\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **Module** | `cmd/cli` |\n| **Language** | Python |\n| **Size** | M (Medium) |\n| **Status** | Proposed |\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement the `KubernetesProvider` and `AgentCubeProvider` classes to enable deployment of AI agents to Kubernetes using either standard K8s resources (Deployment + NodePort Service) or the AgentCube-specific `AgentRuntime` Custom Resource (CR). These providers SHALL serve as the deployment abstraction layer for the AgentCube CLI, enabling seamless publishing of agents to diverse Kubernetes environments.\n\nThe dual-provider architecture SHALL:\n- Support standard Kubernetes deployments for generic K8s clusters\n- Support AgentRuntime CR deployments for AgentCube-enabled clusters\n- Provide consistent interfaces for deploy, status, and delete operations\n- Handle Kubernetes client initialization with fallback to in-cluster config\n- Ensure namespace management and resource lifecycle operations\n- Integrate with the CLI's `publish`, `invoke`, and `status` commands\n\n---\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n1. **KubernetesProvider — Standard K8s Resources**\n   - `deploy_agent()` — Create or update Deployment + NodePort Service\n   - `wait_for_deployment_ready()` — Poll for deployment readiness with timeout\n   - `get_agent_status()` — Retrieve deployment and service status\n   - `delete_agent()` — Remove Deployment and Service resources\n   - Support for configurable replicas, node_port, and environment variables\n   - Proper handling of entrypoint command/args parsing\n\n2. **AgentCubeProvider — AgentRuntime CR**\n   - `deploy_agent_runtime()` — Create or update AgentRuntime Custom Resource\n   - `get_agent_status()` — Retrieve AgentRuntime CR status\n   - `delete_agent()` — Delete AgentRuntime CR\n   - Support for readiness probes, workload manager URL, and router URL\n   - Environment variable injection for AgentCube components\n   - Image pull secrets configuration (default: `default-secret`)\n   - Session timeout and max session duration configuration\n\n3. **Kubernetes Client Management**\n   - Lazy initialization of Kubernetes client\n   - Kubeconfig loading with fallback to in-cluster configuration\n   - Proper error handling for missing `kubernetes` Python library\n   - Namespace existence verification and auto-creation\n   - Support for both `AppsV1Api` and `CustomObjectsApi`\n\n4. **Resource Specification Building**\n   - `_create_or_update_deployment()` — Build Deployment spec\n   - `_create_or_update_service()` — Build NodePort Service spec\n   - `_build_agent_runtime_spec()` — Build AgentRuntime CR spec\n   - `_apply_agent_runtime_cr()` — Apply CR via CustomObjectsApi\n   - Label-based selector consistency across resources\n\n5. **Configuration Handling**\n   - Namespace configuration (default: `default`)\n   - Image URL and port configuration\n   - Entrypoint parsing (command + args split)\n   - Environment variable dictionary support\n   - Optional NodePort assignment (30000-32767 range validation)\n   - Replica count configuration\n\n6. **Error Handling & Logging**\n   - Structured logging via `self.logger`\n   - `RuntimeError` for K8s client initialization failures\n   - `ValueError` for invalid node_port or missing required URLs\n   - `TimeoutError` for deployment readiness timeout\n   - Graceful handling of NotFoundException for idempotent deletes\n\n### Out of Scope\n\n1. **Helm Chart Support**: No Helm packaging or templating\n2. **Operator Development**: Not building an actual K8s operator, just a client\n3. **Multi-Cluster Management**: Single cluster context per provider instance\n4. **RBAC Management**: No role or service account creation\n5. **Ingress Configuration**: No Ingress or Gateway API resources\n6. **HPA/VPA**: No horizontal or vertical pod autoscaler setup\n7. **Pod Disruption Budgets**: No PDB resource management\n8. **Network Policies**: No network policy configuration\n9. **StatefulSet Support**: Only Deployment-based workloads\n10. **Custom Webhook Handling**: No admission webhook management\n\n---\n\n## Design\n\n### Provider Class Hierarchy\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────┐\n│     Abstract Deployment Pattern     │\n├─────────────────────────────────────┤\n│ + deploy()                          │\n│ + get_status()                      │\n│ + delete()                          │\n└──────────────┬──────────────────────┘\n               │\n       ┌───────┴───────┐\n       ▼               ▼\n┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐\n│ Kubernetes   │  │ AgentCube        │\n│ Provider     │  │ Provider         │\n├──────────────┤  ├──────────────────┤\n│ Deployment   │  │ AgentRuntime CR  │\n│ + Service    │  ├──────────────────┤\n├──────────────┤  │ - router_url     │\n│ - namespace  │  │ - workload_mgr   │\n│ - replicas   │  │ - readinessProbe │\n│ - node_port  │  │ - imagePullSecrets│\n└──────────────┘  └──────────────────┘\n```\n\n### KubernetesProvider Structure\n\n```python\nclass KubernetesProvider:\n    def __init__(self, namespace: str = \"default\", verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n    \"\"\"Initialize with namespace and verbosity settings.\"\"\"\n\n    def _get_k8s_client(self) -> Any: ...\n    \"\"\"Lazy-load Kubernetes client with config fallback.\"\"\"\n\n    def _ensure_namespace(self) -> None: ...\n    \"\"\"Create namespace if it doesn't exist.\"\"\"\n\n    def deploy_agent(\n        self,\n        agent_name: str,\n        image_url: str,\n        port: int,\n        entrypoint: Optional[str] = None,\n        replicas: int = 1,\n        node_port: Optional[int] = None,\n        env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n    ) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    \"\"\"Deploy as Deployment + NodePort Service.\"\"\"\n\n    def _create_or_update_deployment(...) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    \"\"\"Build and apply Deployment resource.\"\"\"\n\n    def _create_or_update_service(...) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    \"\"\"Build and apply NodePort Service resource.\"\"\"\n\n    def wait_for_deployment_ready(\n        self, name: str, timeout: int = 120, interval: int = 5\n    ) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    \"\"\"Poll deployment status until ready or timeout.\"\"\"\n\n    def get_agent_status(self, name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    \"\"\"Get deployment and service status.\"\"\"\n\n    def delete_agent(self, name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    \"\"\"Delete deployment and service resources.\"\"\"\n```\n\n### AgentCubeProvider Structure\n\n```python\nclass AgentCubeProvider:\n    def __init__(self, namespace: str = \"default\", verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n    \"\"\"Initialize AgentCube-specific provider.\"\"\"\n\n    def _get_k8s_client(self) -> Any: ...\n    \"\"\"Lazy-load Kubernetes client.\"\"\"\n\n    def _ensure_namespace(self) -> None: ...\n    \"\"\"Ensure namespace exists.\"\"\"\n\n    def deploy_agent_runtime(\n        self,\n        agent_name: str,\n        image_url: str,\n        port: int,\n        entrypoint: Optional[str] = None,\n        env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n        workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = None,\n        readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = None,\n        session_timeout: str = \"15m\",\n        max_session_duration: str = \"8h\",\n        image_pull_secrets: Optional[list] = None,\n    ) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    \"\"\"Deploy AgentRuntime Custom Resource.\"\"\"\n\n    def _build_agent_runtime_spec(...) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    \"\"\"Build AgentRuntime CR specification dictionary.\"\"\"\n\n    def _apply_agent_runtime_cr(self, agent_name: str, cr_spec: Dict[str, Any]) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    \"\"\"Apply CR using CustomObjectsApi.\"\"\"\n\n    def get_agent_status(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    \"\"\"Get AgentRuntime CR status.\"\"\"\n\n    def delete_agent(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    \"\"\"Delete AgentRuntime CR.\"\"\"\n```\n\n### Kubernetes Client Initialization Flow\n\n```\n_get_k8s_client()\n    │\n    ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────┐\n│ Check cached client         │\n│ (self._k8s_client)          │\n└─────────────┬───────────────┘\n              │ Exists\n              ▼\n       ┌──────────────┐\n       │ Return cached │\n       └───────────────┘\n              │ Not exists\n              ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────┐\n│ Try import kubernetes       │\n│ (client, config)            │\n└─────────────┬───────────────┘\n              │ ImportError\n              ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────┐\n│ Raise RuntimeError          │\n│ \"pip install kubernetes\"    │\n└─────────────────────────────┘\n              │ Success\n              ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────┐\n│ Try load_kube_config()      │\n└─────────────┬───────────────┘\n              │ Success\n              ▼\n       ┌──────────────┐\n       │ Log \"kubeconfig\"│\n       └──────┬─────────┘\n              │ Failure\n              ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────┐\n│ Try load_incluster_config() │\n└─────────────┬───────────────┘\n              │ Success\n              ▼\n       ┌──────────────┐\n       │ Log \"in-cluster\"│\n       └──────┬─────────┘\n              │ Failure\n              ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────┐\n│ Raise RuntimeError          │\n│ \"Failed to load K8s config\" │\n└─────────────────────────────┘\n              │\n              ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────┐\n│ Initialize APIs             │\n│ - AppsV1Api                 │\n│ - CoreV1Api                 │\n│ - CustomObjectsApi          │\n└─────────────┬───────────────┘\n              │\n              ▼\n       ┌──────────────┐\n       │ Return client │\n       └───────────────┘\n```\n\n### Deployment Flow (KubernetesProvider)\n\n```\ndeploy_agent(agent_name, image_url, port, ...)\n    │\n    ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────┐\n│ Validate node_port range    │\n│ (30000-32767 if provided)   │\n└─────────────┬───────────────┘\n              │ Invalid\n              ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────┐\n│ Raise ValueError            │\n└─────────────────────────────┘\n              │ Valid\n              ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────┐\n│ _get_k8s_client()           │\n└─────────────┬───────────────┘\n              │\n              ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────┐\n│ _ensure_namespace()         │\n└─────────────┬───────────────┘\n              │\n              ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────┐\n│ _create_or_update_deployment│\n│ - Build V1Deployment        │\n│ - Try update, catch 404     │\n│ - Create if not exists      │\n└─────────────┬───────────────┘\n              │\n              ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────┐\n│ _create_or_update_service   │\n│ - Build V1Service (NodePort)│\n│ - Try update, catch 404     │\n│ - Create if not exists      │\n└─────────────┬───────────────┘\n              │\n              ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────┐\n│ Build result dict           │\n│ - deployment_name           │\n│ - service_name              │\n│ - node_port                 │\n│ - service_url               │\n│ - status: \"deployed\"        │\n└─────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### AgentRuntime CR Structure\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: agentcube.io/v1\nkind: AgentRuntime\nmetadata:\n  name: {agent_name}\n  namespace: {namespace}\nspec:\n  image: {image_url}\n  port: {port}\n  sessionTimeout: \"15m\"\n  maxSessionDuration: \"8h\"\n  podTemplate:\n    spec:\n      imagePullSecrets:\n        - name: default-secret\n      containers:\n        - name: {agent_name}\n          image: {image_url}\n          ports:\n            - containerPort: {port}\n          env:\n            - name: WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\n              value: {workload_manager_url}\n            - name: ROUTER_URL\n              value: {router_url}\n          command: [{entrypoint_command}]  # if entrypoint provided\n          args: [{entrypoint_args}]        # if args exist\n          readinessProbe:                  # if readiness_probe_path set\n            httpGet:\n              path: {readiness_probe_path}\n              port: {readiness_probe_port}\n            initialDelaySeconds: 10\n            periodSeconds: 5\n```\n\n---\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Affected Components\n\n| Component | Impact | Description |\n|-----------|--------|-------------|\n| `PublishRuntime` | High | Uses both providers for `publish` command |\n| `StatusRuntime` | High | Uses both providers for `status` command |\n| `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Medium | `--provider` flag affects provider selection |\n| `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py` | High | New file for KubernetesProvider |\n| `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py` | High | New file for AgentCubeProvider |\n| `agentcube/services/__init__.py` | Low | May export provider classes |\n| `pyproject.toml` | Low | Optional `kubernetes` dependency |\n\n### Deployment Configuration Changes\n\n**Standard K8s Deployment Result:**\n```python\n{\n    \"deployment_name\": \"my-agent\",\n    \"service_name\": \"my-agent\",\n    \"namespace\": \"default\",\n    \"node_port\": 30080,\n    \"replicas\": 1,\n    \"service_url\": \"http://localhost:30080\",\n    \"status\": \"deployed\",\n}\n```\n\n**AgentRuntime CR Deployment Result:**\n```python\n{\n    \"agent_id\": \"my-agent\",\n    \"agent_endpoint\": \"http://router:8080/v1/agents/my-agent\",\n    \"name\": \"my-agent\",\n    \"namespace\": \"default\",\n    \"status\": \"deployed\",\n    \"workload_manager_url\": \"http://workload-manager:8080\",\n    \"router_url\": \"http://router:8080\",\n}\n```\n\n### Error Scenarios\n\n| Scenario | Exception | Message Pattern |\n|----------|-----------|-----------------|\n| K8s library not installed | `RuntimeError` | \"Kubernetes client library not installed\" |\n| K8s config load failure | `RuntimeError` | \"Failed to load Kubernetes configuration\" |\n| Invalid node_port | `ValueError` | \"NodePort must be in range 30000-32767\" |\n| Deployment timeout | `TimeoutError` | \"did not become ready within {timeout} seconds\" |\n| Missing AgentCube URLs | `ValueError` | \"requires router_url and workload_manager_url\" |\n| Deployment failure | `RuntimeError` | \"Deployment {name} failed: {message}\" |\n| CR apply failure | `RuntimeError` | \"Failed to deploy AgentRuntime: {e}\" |\n| Resource not found | Returns dict | `{\"status\": \"not_found\"}` |\n\n---\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Alternative 1: Single Unified Provider\n\n**Approach**: Combine both providers into a single class with mode flags.\n\n**Rejected**: Separation of concerns. Standard K8s and AgentRuntime CR have fundamentally different deployment models, configuration requirements, and status checking mechanisms. Keeping them separate allows independent evolution and clearer code organization.\n\n### Alternative 2: kubectl CLI Invocation\n\n**Approach**: Use subprocess to call `kubectl` commands instead of Python kubernetes client.\n\n**Rejected**: Less efficient, harder to parse results, requires kubectl binary in PATH, less type-safe. Using the official Python client provides better error handling, structured responses, and integrates better with the CLI's Python codebase.\n\n### Alternative 3: Helm-based Deployment\n\n**Approach**: Use Helm charts for deployment instead of direct API calls.\n\n**Rejected**: Adds Helm as a dependency, overkill for simple deployments, harder to customize per-deployment parameters programmatically. Direct API calls provide more control and fewer external dependencies.\n\n### Alternative 4: Kubernetes Operator\n\n**Approach**: Build a full Kubernetes operator with CRDs and controllers.\n\n**Rejected**: Too complex for CLI tool requirements. An operator would require cluster-admin setup, separate deployment process, and ongoing maintenance. The current approach uses the existing AgentRuntime CRD without requiring operator installation.\n\n### Alternative 5: Server-side Apply Only\n\n**Approach**: Use only server-side apply (SSA) for all resource updates.\n\n**Deferred**: While SSA is modern best practice, the client library's support and complexity don't justify the migration for this use case. The current create-or-update pattern is well-understood and reliable.\n\n### Alternative 6: Support for Additional Workload Types\n\n**Approach**: Support DaemonSet, Job, CronJob in addition to Deployment.\n\n**Rejected**: Out of scope for agent deployment use cases. Agents are long-running services best modeled as Deployments. Can be added later if requirements change.\n\n---\n\n## Verification\n\n### KubernetesProvider Deployment Verification\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube.services.k8s_provider import KubernetesProvider\n\n# Initialize provider\nprovider = KubernetesProvider(namespace=\"default\", verbose=True)\n\n# Deploy agent\nresult = provider.deploy_agent(\n    agent_name=\"test-agent\",\n    image_url=\"nginx:latest\",\n    port=8080,\n    replicas=2,\n    node_port=30080,\n)\n\nprint(f\"Deployment: {result['deployment_name']}\")\nprint(f\"Service URL: {result['service_url']}\")\n\n# Wait for readiness\ntry:\n    status = provider.wait_for_deployment_ready(\"test-agent\", timeout=120)\n    print(f\"Ready: {status['ready_replicas']}/{status['desired_replicas']}\")\nexcept TimeoutError as e:\n    print(f\"Timeout: {e}\")\n```\n\n### AgentCubeProvider Deployment Verification\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube.services.agentcube_provider import AgentCubeProvider\n\n# Initialize provider\nprovider = AgentCubeProvider(namespace=\"default\", verbose=True)\n\n# Deploy AgentRuntime CR\nresult = provider.deploy_agent_runtime(\n    agent_name=\"my-agent\",\n    image_url=\"my-registry/agent:v1.0.0\",\n    port=8080,\n    workload_manager_url=\"http://workload-manager:8080\",\n    router_url=\"http://router:8080\",\n    readiness_probe_path=\"/health\",\n    session_timeout=\"30m\",\n)\n\nprint(f\"Agent ID: {result['agent_id']}\")\nprint(f\"Endpoint: {result['agent_endpoint']}\")\n```\n\n### Status Check Verification\n\n```python\n# Check K8s provider status\nstatus = provider.get_agent_status(\"test-agent\")\nprint(f\"Replicas: {status['deployment']['ready_replicas']}/{status['deployment']['replicas']}\")\nprint(f\"NodePort: {status['service']['node_port']}\")\n\n# Check AgentCube provider status\nstatus = provider.get_agent_status(\"my-agent\")\nprint(f\"Status: {status['status']}\")\n```\n\n### Cleanup Verification\n\n```python\n# Delete resources\nresult = provider.delete_agent(\"test-agent\")\nprint(f\"Deployment deleted: {result['deployment_deleted']}\")\nprint(f\"Service deleted: {result['service_deleted']}\")\n\n# Idempotent delete (no error if not exists)\nresult = provider.delete_agent(\"non-existent\")\nprint(f\"Status: {result}\")  # Shows not_found, no exception\n```\n\n### Error Handling Verification\n\n```python\n# Invalid node_port\ntry:\n    provider.deploy_agent(\n        agent_name=\"test\",\n        image_url=\"nginx:latest\",\n        port=8080,\n        node_port=1000,  # Invalid range\n    )\nexcept ValueError as e:\n    print(f\"Expected error: {e}\")\n\n# Missing URLs for AgentCube\ntry:\n    agentcube_provider.deploy_agent_runtime(\n        agent_name=\"test\",\n        image_url=\"nginx:latest\",\n        port=8080,\n        # Missing workload_manager_url and router_url\n    )\nexcept ValueError as e:\n    print(f\"Expected error: {e}\")\n```\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- [cli-toolkit/design.md](cli-toolkit/design.md) — CLI package layout and provider architecture\n- [cli-toolkit/spec.md](cli-toolkit/spec.md) — Provider requirements specification\n- [deployment/client-go.md](deployment/client-go.md) — AgentRuntime CR API specification\n- [Kubernetes Python Client Documentation](https://github.com/kubernetes-client/python) — Official Python client docs\n- [Kubernetes Deployment Documentation](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/workloads/controllers/deployment/) — K8s Deployment concepts\n- [Custom Resources](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/extend-kubernetes/api-extension/custom-resources/) — CRD concepts\n- AR-020 — CLI Pack Command (precedes publish)\n- AR-021 — CLI Build Command (precedes publish)\n- AR-022 — CLI Publish Command (uses providers)\n- AR-023 — CLI Invoke/Status Commands (uses providers)\n- AR-024 — DockerService Encapsulation (related service pattern)\n- AR-025 — MetadataService (provides deployment parameters)\n\n---\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n1. ✅ `KubernetesProvider` class exists in `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py`\n2. ✅ `AgentCubeProvider` class exists in `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py`\n3. ✅ Both providers have `namespace` and `verbose` constructor parameters\n4. ✅ `_get_k8s_client()` implements lazy initialization with config fallback\n5. ✅ `_ensure_namespace()` creates namespace if it doesn't exist\n6. ✅ `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent()` creates Deployment + NodePort Service\n7. ✅ `KubernetesProvider.wait_for_deployment_ready()` polls with timeout\n8. ✅ `KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status()` returns deployment and service status\n9. ✅ `KubernetesProvider.delete_agent()` removes both resources\n10. ✅ `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime()` creates AgentRuntime CR\n11. ✅ AgentRuntime CR includes required environment variables (WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL, ROUTER_URL)\n12. ✅ AgentRuntime CR includes default imagePullSecrets (`default-secret`)\n13. ✅ Readiness probe is configured when readiness_probe_path is provided\n14. ✅ Session timeout defaults to \"15m\" and max duration to \"8h\"\n15. ✅ `AgentCubeProvider.get_agent_status()` returns CR status\n16. ✅ `AgentCubeProvider.delete_agent()` deletes the CR\n17. ✅ Entrypoint parsing correctly splits into command and args\n18. ✅ NodePort validation enforces 30000-32767 range\n19. ✅ Missing AgentCube URLs raise `ValueError` with clear message\n20. ✅ Kubernetes client initialization errors raise `RuntimeError`\n21. ✅ Both providers use structured logging via `self.logger`\n22. ✅ Providers are importable from `agentcube.services`\n23. ✅ NotFoundException during delete is handled gracefully (idempotent)\n24. ✅ Deployment timeout raises `TimeoutError` with descriptive message\n\n---\n\n*AR-026 — Module: cmd/cli — Language: Python — Size: M*\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py\">\nERROR [80:27] \"read_namespace\" is not a known attribute of \"None\"\nERROR [85:27] \"create_namespace\" is not a known attribute of \"None\"\nERROR [238:38] \"read_namespaced_deployment\" is not a known attribute of \"None\"\nERROR [246:40] \"replace_namespaced_deployment\" is not a known attribute of \"None\"\nERROR [256:36] \"create_namespaced_deployment\" is not a known attribute of \"None\"\nERROR [310:38] \"read_namespaced_service\" is not a known attribute of \"None\"\nERROR [318:40] \"replace_namespaced_service\" is not a known attribute of \"None\"\nERROR [328:36] \"create_namespaced_service\" is not a known attribute of \"None\"\nERROR [336:30] Cannot access attribute \"spec\" for class \"str\"\n  Attribute \"spec\" is unknown\nERROR [336:30] Cannot access attribute \"spec\" for class \"list[list[Unknown] | dict[Unknown, list[Unknown] | dict[Unknown, Unknown] | Unknown | str | _Date | datetime | None] | Unknown | str | _Date | datetime | None]\"\n  Attribute \"spec\" is unknown\nERROR [336: