{"type":"text","timestamp":1775899434948,"sessionID":"ses_2842c4eeeffe5EI9bM3M8UmhOg","part":{"id":"prt_d7bdadb78001rBtqtpr3uzvnxk","messageID":"msg_d7bdabb15001NszPmVPjphG4J3","sessionID":"ses_2842c4eeeffe5EI9bM3M8UmhOg","type":"text","text":"I've successfully written the `proposal.md` file for AR-026 — K8s/AgentCube Provider. Let me verify the file:","time":{"start":1775899434946,"end":1775899434946}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775899439190,"sessionID":"ses_2842c4eeeffe5EI9bM3M8UmhOg","part":{"id":"prt_d7bdadfc5001NL2Wh55O6YfgoA","messageID":"msg_d7bdabb15001NszPmVPjphG4J3","sessionID":"ses_2842c4eeeffe5EI9bM3M8UmhOg","type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"toolu_functions.bash:14","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"head -100 /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","description":"Verify proposal.md content"},"output":"# Proposal: K8s/AgentCube Provider (AR-026)\n\n## AR-026 — K8s/AgentCube Provider\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **Module** | `cmd/cli` |\n| **Language** | Python |\n| **Size** | M (Medium) |\n| **Status** | Proposed |\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement the `KubernetesProvider` and `AgentCubeProvider` classes to enable deployment of AI agents to Kubernetes using either standard K8s resources (Deployment + NodePort Service) or the AgentCube-specific `AgentRuntime` Custom Resource (CR). These providers SHALL serve as the deployment abstraction layer for the AgentCube CLI, enabling seamless publishing of agents to diverse Kubernetes environments.\n\nThe dual-provider architecture SHALL:\n- Support standard Kubernetes deployments for generic K8s clusters\n- Support AgentRuntime CR deployments for AgentCube-enabled clusters\n- Provide consistent interfaces for deploy, status, and delete operations\n- Handle Kubernetes client initialization with fallback to in-cluster config\n- Ensure namespace management and resource lifecycle operations\n- Integrate with the CLI's `publish`, `invoke`, and `status` commands\n\n---\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n1. **KubernetesProvider — Standard K8s Resources**\n   - `deploy_agent()` — Create or update Deployment + NodePort Service\n   - `wait_for_deployment_ready()` — Poll for deployment readiness with timeout\n   - `get_agent_status()` — Retrieve deployment and service status\n   - `delete_agent()` — Remove Deployment and Service resources\n   - Support for configurable replicas, node_port, and environment variables\n   - Proper handling of entrypoint command/args parsing\n\n2. **AgentCubeProvider — AgentRuntime CR**\n   - `deploy_agent_runtime()` — Create or update AgentRuntime Custom Resource\n   - `get_agent_status()` — Retrieve AgentRuntime CR status\n   - `delete_agent()` — Delete AgentRuntime CR\n   - Support for readiness probes, workload manager URL, and router URL\n   - Environment variable injection for AgentCube components\n   - Image pull secrets configuration (default: `default-secret`)\n   - Session timeout and max session duration configuration\n\n3. **Kubernetes Client Management**\n   - Lazy initialization of Kubernetes client\n   - Kubeconfig loading with fallback to in-cluster configuration\n   - Proper error handling for missing `kubernetes` Python library\n   - Namespace existence verification and auto-creation\n   - Support for both `AppsV1Api` and `CustomObjectsApi`\n\n4. **Resource Specification Building**\n   - `_create_or_update_deployment()` — Build Deployment spec\n   - `_create_or_update_service()` — Build NodePort Service spec\n   - `_build_agent_runtime_spec()` — Build AgentRuntime CR spec\n   - `_apply_agent_runtime_cr()` — Apply CR via CustomObjectsApi\n   - Label-based selector consistency across resources\n\n5. **Configuration Handling**\n   - Namespace configuration (default: `default`)\n   - Image URL and port configuration\n   - Entrypoint parsing (command + args split)\n   - Environment variable dictionary support\n   - Optional NodePort assignment (30000-32767 range validation)\n   - Replica count configuration\n\n6. **Error Handling & Logging**\n   - Structured logging via `self.logger`\n   - `RuntimeError` for K8s client initialization failures\n   - `ValueError` for invalid node_port or missing required URLs\n   - `TimeoutError` for deployment readiness timeout\n   - Graceful handling of NotFoundException for idempotent deletes\n\n### Out of Scope\n\n1. **Helm Chart Support**: No Helm packaging or templating\n2. **Operator Development**: Not building an actual K8s operator, just a client\n3. **Multi-Cluster Management**: Single cluster context per provider instance\n4. **RBAC Management**: No role or service account creation\n5. **Ingress Configuration**: No Ingress or Gateway API resources\n6. **HPA/VPA**: No horizontal or vertical pod autoscaler setup\n7. **Pod Disruption Budgets**: No PDB resource management\n8. **Network Policies**: No network policy configuration\n9. **StatefulSet Support**: Only Deployment-based workloads\n10. **Custom Webhook Handling**: No admission webhook management\n\n---\n\n## Design\n\n### Provider Class Hierarchy\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────┐\n│     Abstract Deployment Pattern     │\n├─────────────────────────────────────┤\n","metadata":{"output":"# Proposal: K8s/AgentCube Provider (AR-026)\n\n## AR-026 — K8s/AgentCube Provider\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **Module** | `cmd/cli` |\n| **Language** | Python |\n| **Size** | M (Medium) |\n| **Status** | Proposed |\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement the `KubernetesProvider` and `AgentCubeProvider` classes to enable deployment of AI agents to Kubernetes using either standard K8s resources (Deployment + NodePort Service) or the AgentCube-specific `AgentRuntime` Custom Resource (CR). These providers SHALL serve as the deployment abstraction layer for the AgentCube CLI, enabling seamless publishing of agents to diverse Kubernetes environments.\n\nThe dual-provider architecture SHALL:\n- Support standard Kubernetes deployments for generic K8s clusters\n- Support AgentRuntime CR deployments for AgentCube-enabled clusters\n- Provide consistent interfaces for deploy, status, and delete operations\n- Handle Kubernetes client initialization with fallback to in-cluster config\n- Ensure namespace management and resource lifecycle operations\n- Integrate with the CLI's `publish`, `invoke`, and `status` commands\n\n---\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n1. **KubernetesProvider — Standard K8s Resources**\n   - `deploy_agent()` — Create or update Deployment + NodePort Service\n   - `wait_for_deployment_ready()` — Poll for deployment readiness with timeout\n   - `get_agent_status()` — Retrieve deployment and service status\n   - `delete_agent()` — Remove Deployment and Service resources\n   - Support for configurable replicas, node_port, and environment variables\n   - Proper handling of entrypoint command/args parsing\n\n2. **AgentCubeProvider — AgentRuntime CR**\n   - `deploy_agent_runtime()` — Create or update AgentRuntime Custom Resource\n   - `get_agent_status()` — Retrieve AgentRuntime CR status\n   - `delete_agent()` — Delete AgentRuntime CR\n   - Support for readiness probes, workload manager URL, and router URL\n   - Environment variable injection for AgentCube components\n   - Image pull secrets configuration (default: `default-secret`)\n   - Session timeout and max session duration configuration\n\n3. **Kubernetes Client Management**\n   - Lazy initialization of Kubernetes client\n   - Kubeconfig loading with fallback to in-cluster configuration\n   - Proper error handling for missing `kubernetes` Python library\n   - Namespace existence verification and auto-creation\n   - Support for both `AppsV1Api` and `CustomObjectsApi`\n\n4. **Resource Specification Building**\n   - `_create_or_update_deployment()` — Build Deployment spec\n   - `_create_or_update_service()` — Build NodePort Service spec\n   - `_build_agent_runtime_spec()` — Build AgentRuntime CR spec\n   - `_apply_agent_runtime_cr()` — Apply CR via CustomObjectsApi\n   - Label-based selector consistency across resources\n\n5. **Configuration Handling**\n   - Namespace configuration (default: `default`)\n   - Image URL and port configuration\n   - Entrypoint parsing (command + args split)\n   - Environment variable dictionary support\n   - Optional NodePort assignment (30000-32767 range validation)\n   - Replica